                <description>&lt;h2 id=&quot;enabling-wifi-on-boot-for-hidden-ssids&quot;&gt;Enabling wifi on boot for hidden ssids&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;strong&gt;&#x2F;etc&#x2F;NetworkManager&#x2F;NetworkManger.conf&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;, under the &lt;strong&gt;[wifi]&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; section add &lt;strong&gt;hidden=true&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To test if the changes worked, you can do either of the following:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
    &lt;li&gt; Restart NetworkManager by running `sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager` &lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt; Reboot your system by running `sudo reboot` &lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your system should now automatically scan and connect to your hidden ssid!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</description>
